Potential Data Leakage Alert

Indicates that a value in an explanatory variable always results in the same outcome value, which can indicate data leakage. To produce more realistic models that perform better at predicting outcomes, investigate and remove leaky predictor variables from your model.

Actions to Consider
Investigate the variable for data leakage. If found, exclude the variable from the model.

Einstein Discovery automatically alerts you when it detects that an explanatory variable always leads to the same outcome.
